Package io.github.noeppi_noeppi.libx.mod.registration

Interface Registerable

All Known Implementing Classes:
BlockBase, BlockBE, BlockMenu, EnumObjects, FluidBase
public interface Registerable
Everything that is registered to ModXRegistration that implements this can specify dependencies and things to be done during setup phase.

  • Method Details

    • getAdditionalRegisters

      default Set<Object> getAdditionalRegisters​(net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation id)
      Gets additional items that should be registered. Those may be Registerable as well. These objects will be registered with the same id as this registerable.

    • getNamedAdditionalRegisters

      default Map<String,​Object> getNamedAdditionalRegisters​(net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation id)
      Gets additional items that should be registered. Those may be Registerable as well. These objects will be registered with the id of this registerable appended by their key in the map. This allows to register multiple thing to the same registry.

    • registerCommon

      default void registerCommon​(net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation id, Consumer<Runnable> defer)
      Do stuff needed in the setup phase. This is called during parallel mod loading.
      Parameters:
      defer - Pass a runnable to this to defer it to the synchronous work queue.

    • registerClient

      default void registerClient​(net.minecraft.resources.ResourceLocation id, Consumer<Runnable> defer)
      Do stuff needed on the client. This is called during parallel mod loading.
      Parameters:
      defer - Pass a runnable to this to defer it to the synchronous work queue.
